{"source_key":"sha256-784c2f10bfe4a26d66c37ad545f72f01","record_index":29702,"record_hash":"sha256:3ac5d8fe3681ce17ee0935d29acabc877506b1813788ec6b10b907b535f79fe0","timestamp":"2026-05-11T14:22:16.927Z","kind":"message","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:message","role":"user","text":"<subagent_notification>\n{\"agent_path\":\"[REDACTED:entropy]\",\"status\":{\"completed\":\"**Findings**\\n\\n- **P1: `agentlog hook` can fail before reaching its documented missing-transcript no-op.**  \\n  The outer CLI normalizes/validates `agent` before `but_agentlog::run_from_dir` reads the hook payload: [crates/but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1485). If no supported agent is detected, it bails at [crates/but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1509). That means the inner no-op for missing/empty `transcript_path` at [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:91) is unreachable unless `--agent` or env detection succeeds, despite the hook workflow saying missing `transcript_path` exits successfully: [[REDACTED:entropy].md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:31). I reproduced this with a missing-transcript hook payload: it exits `1` with `agentlog requires --agent when no supported agent is detected`.\\n\\n- **P2: GitMeta session/source metadata is written before the transcript append/hash update can still fail.**  \\n  `write_transcript_batch` writes `gitbutler:agent-sessions`, schema, updated-at, sources, and source fields at [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:73), then only later serializes transcript records and applies transcript/hash edits at [crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/gitmeta.rs:87). If serialization or `apply_edits` fails, callers get an error but GitMeta may already contain a session index/source record without the transcript append. A small improvement is to build/serialize all transcript entries and preflight risky collection state before the first GitMeta mutation.\\n\\n- **P3: `cli.rs` owns non-CLI capture orchestration.**  \\n  `record_agent_log` in [crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/cli.rs:108) discovers the repo, canonicalizes the workdir, resolves transcript paths, calls capture, and performs association. That crosses the documented module boundary where `cli.rs` should map CLI inputs and `capture.rs` should own orchestration/source identity: [agent-session-capture/architecture.md](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/agent-session-capture/architecture.md:46). Moving this helper into `capture.rs` would keep the public command layer thinner without changing behavior.\\n\\n- **P3: Codex extraction/pruning path lists are manually duplicated.**  \\n  The same provider path vocabulary is repeated across text extraction, tool-input extraction, and pruning: [crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:229), [crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:254), and [crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:271). If one list changes without the matching prune list, stored records can either duplicate normalized payloads or drop uncopied data. Constants or returning the matched path from extraction would reduce code and drift risk.\\n\\n**Validation**\\n\\nRead-only review; no files edited. Ran `cargo test -p but-agentlog` successfully: 22 tests passed. Also compiled/exercised the top-level `but --features agentlog agentlog hook` path for the missing-transcript ordering repro.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T14:22:16.927Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}